# --- Contact / custom-order form delivery ------------------------------
# Forms are sent via FormSubmit (https://formsubmit.co) — a free service that
# emails you each submission and supports file attachments (reference photos).
# No backend needed.
#
# Setup:
# 1. Decide which inbox should receive enquiries (Nicky's email).
# 2. (Recommended) Get a random alias so the email isn't exposed on the site:
#    submit any FormSubmit form to the address once, confirm the activation
#    email, then copy the alias string (looks like "abc123…") from the email.
# 3. Put the alias (or, less private, the raw email) below.
# 4. For PRODUCTION (GitHub Pages): add it as a repo secret named FORMSUBMIT_ID
#    (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions). The deploy workflow passes it
#    in as NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSUBMIT_ID at build time.
#
# Until this is set, the forms show a "please call" message instead of sending.
NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSUBMIT_ID=

# --- Hosting base path -------------------------------------------------
# Only needed if you build/preview the production export locally. The GitHub
# Actions workflow sets this automatically to "/<repo-name>". Leave blank for
# local "npm run dev".
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=/Nicky_B
